Outline of what each method does in the Cartique class:

 Constructor & Core Methods
- constructor(): Initializes the class with products and features, sets up defaults
- deepMerge(): Helper for deep merging objects (features configuration)
- isObject(): Checks if item is a plain object
- debounce(): Creates debounced functions for performance (search input)
- addEventListener(): Wrapper for addEventListener with cleanup tracking

 Initialization & Setup
- init(): Main initialization method - sets up container, themes, templates
- applyMinimalTheme(): Applies theme settings to maintain original design
- injectCriticalCSS(): Injects minimal CSS for initial display
- completeInitialization(): Finalizes initialization by making container visible

 Template & DOM Management
- fetchAndExtractComponents(): Gets HTML templates from DOM template holder
- renderAllComponents(): Orchestrates rendering of all UI components
- renderMainFrame(): Creates main container structure with sidebar/main/footer
- renderSidebar(): Renders sidebar with filter components
- renderControls(): Renders search, sort, view toggle, and cart icon controls
- renderProductDisplays(): Sets up grid/list product display containers
- renderFooter(): Renders pagination footer
- renderCartSlider(): Creates shopping cart slide-out panel
- renderCartItemTemplate(): Creates template for cart items

 Product Display & Rendering
- renderProducts(): Renders products in current layout (grid/list)
- createProductCard(): Creates individual grid product card
- createProductListing(): Creates individual list product item
- updateProductElement(): Populates product data into DOM elements
- setLayout(): Switches between grid and list views

 Event Handlers & User Interactions
- setupEventListeners(): Sets up layout toggle events
- cleanupEventListeners(): Removes all event listeners for cleanup
- handleSearch(): Filters products based on search query
- handleSort(): Sorts products by selected criteria (price/title)
- showSingleProductView(): Shows detailed single product view
- renderSingleProduct(): Renders detailed product page with tabs
- returnToListView(): Returns from single product view to main listing

 Shopping Cart Operations
- addToCart(): Adds product to cart (localStorage)
- showCart(): Displays cart slide-out with current items
- updateCartItem(): Updates cart item DOM with product data
- addCartItemEventListeners(): Adds events to cart items (remove/qty)
- removeCartItem(): Removes item from cart
- decreaseQtyItem(): Decreases cart item quantity
- increaseQtyItem(): Increases cart item quantity
- closeCart(): Closes cart slide-out

 Checkout & Notifications
- checkout(): Initiates checkout process
- showCheckoutAlert(): Shows success toast and redirects
- clearToastTimeouts(): Cleans up notification timers

 Utility & Error Handling
- showErrorMessage(): Displays error messages to user
- destroy(): Cleanup method for component removal

The class follows a modular structure with clear separation: initialization, template rendering, product display, cart management, and event handling.